reviews.review: great conclusion to a great series.

If you grew up with Star Wars (I was born in 1972), this movie is great.  It is for the fans.  It was exactly as I expected...typical Star Wars...good guys win with a little loss and hope is a big theme.  Not many surprises, but that is okay.  Lots of adults crying in the theaters while reliving there childhood.
Very enjoyable and a satisfying ending to the Skywalker Saga
This was disappointing.  The plot is pretty much the same as always.  Bummer
By far better than the Last Jedi but far from perfect

I enjoyed the finale to this saga in Star Wars, I had some issues with some of the plot points. I won't go into details cuz it pertains to one of the protagonists However I feel this movie wrapped up several arcs for characters and that was satisfying. How their stories were wrapped up might be a common gripe for this movie. Overall worth the watch but temper expectations.

JJ Abrams was left the near-impossible task of cleaning up the mess of episode VIII & creating a worthy wrap up of the Skywalker saga.  He has achieved this lofty goal with a movie that ranks an 9.0 on it's own & a 9.7 considering what he was left with from VIII.  This is a genuine SW film complete with all our old heros & the new ones in roles worthy of their acting ability.  Luke, Han, Leia, Lando, etc. are there, & at the same time Finn isn't cast as a joke, Rey isn't a 'Mary Sue' & her powers are explained, Poe isn't cast as the incompetent male scolded by the female admiral with purple hair, and all the SJW garbage is gone.  Rey's character is stellar & she indeed is not a 'nobody'.  There is once again a "real" villain.  Luke says he was wrong for becoming a hermit & when a lightsaber is thrown he scolds, saying, "A Jedi weapon should be treated with respect."  Yes, it undos much what we hated about VIII & frankly is a real (and justified) slap in the face to Ryan Johnson.  In a word JJ Abrams "saved" Star Wars.  IMO the entire 9 episode saga might best be viewed with 90% of episode VIII edited out.
It's ok to fuck up your own creation, but to also ruin the last trilogy ending is in another level, i hope this last three movies were just a bad dream.

Rogue One, Solo, and The Mandolorian are very good and the new writers for whatever starwars is coming down the pipes needs to take a look at these projects and see what they got right
